        <updateDate>2021-09-12T15:47:21Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Stop Significant and Time-wasting Abuse Limiting Legitimate Innovation of New Generics Act or the</b> <b>Stop STALLING Act</b></p> <div>This bill makes it an unfair method of competition to submit an objectively baseless petition to the Food and Drug Administration (FDA) in an attempt to interfere with a competitor's application for market approval of a drug.</div> <div><br /></div> <div>The bill authorizes the Federal Trade Commission to sue an individual or entity that submits such a petition to the FDA. A party found liable in such a lawsuit shall be subject to civil penalties, such as a fine of up to $50,000 for each day that the FDA spent reviewing the baseless petition. </div>]]></text>
      </summary>
